{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:29:06.115052+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 761394d4c1bc093dffd57dd9d470512c6d645aaf)", "id": "lc_708b8ed5-1f56-4c64-9e63-4b626562adfb"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Default profile set shipped with vidpack.\n# Edit to customize or add profiles. Profile names must be lowercase ASCII.\n\n[web]\ncontainer = \"mp4\"\nvideo_codec = \"libx264\"\naudio_codec = \"aac\"\nvideo_bitrate = \"2M\"\nscale = \"1280:720\"\n\n[archive]\ncontainer = \"mkv\"\nvideo_codec = \"libx265\"\naudio_codec = \"flac\"\ncrf = 18\nscale = \"source\"\n\n[gif]\ncontainer = \"gif\"\nfps = 12\nscale = \"480:-1\"\n# Note: the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation,\n# which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper\n# two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in\n# the issue tracker.\n", "id": "lc_3c45d138-9c7a-4a17-a648-5962fffa9a8e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "12198300-fe3f-4967-b9f0-deda8dc6fac4", "tool_call_id": "call_bfc0da8acd4243f9a9d59cdb", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:29:06.148141+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: dd8f230ebcee1ed2c87953be052ec8d2681c21fc)", "id": "lc_580a784e-91b3-4d03-8bf3-dbcc0446b3b4"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# vidpack — profile-driven FFmpeg wrapper\n\n`vidpack` is a small Python CLI that runs FFmpeg using named profiles defined\nin `profiles.toml`. The goal is to avoid memorizing long ffmpeg flag strings\nfor routine encoding jobs.\n\nFFmpeg is **not** bundled. `vidpack` expects `ffmpeg` (and `ffprobe`, where\nrelevant) to be available on `PATH`.\n\n## Install\n\n```\npip install -e .\n```\n\nThis registers the `vidpack` command.\n\n## Profiles\n\nThe default `profiles.toml` ships three profiles:\n\n| Profile   | Container | Video codec | Audio codec | Notes                       |\n|-----------|-----------|-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|\n| `web`     | mp4       | libx264     | aac         | 720p, target bitrate 2 Mbps |\n| `archive` | mkv       | libx265     | flac        | source resolution, CRF 18   |\n| `gif`     | gif       | (palette)   | (none)      | 480p wide, 12 fps           |\n\nEdit `profiles.toml` to customize or add profiles.\n\n## Usage\n\n```\nvidpack <profile> <input> [-o OUTPUT] [--dry-run]\n```\n\nIf `-o` is omitted, the output filename is derived from the input by\nreplacing the extension with the profile's container extension.\n\n`--dry-run` prints the ffmpeg command vidpack would run, without executing it.\n\nBy default, vidpack will **not** overwrite an existing output file; it exits\nwith an error. Delete the output manually or pass a different `-o`.\n\n## Examples\n\n```\n# Re-encode an mp4 for web at 720p\nvidpack web input.mov -o talk.mp4\n\n# Lossless-ish archive copy\nvidpack archive input.mov\n\n# Preview the ffmpeg command for the gif profile without running it\nvidpack gif clip.mp4 --dry-run\n```\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n", "id": "lc_cf720c97-5d85-4f07-90c8-517f5e504916"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "af3e6c23-be63-4df3-9655-82d745a681f2", "tool_call_id": "call_fd375e9fd29644b5b7de8fca", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:29:14.999118+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "When a user runs the `vidpack` command in this repository, they can select from **three encoding profiles**, as defined in the default `profiles.toml`. Here's a breakdown:\n\n| Profile    | Container | Video Codec   | Audio Codec |\n|------------|-----------|---------------|-------------|\n| **`web`**      | `.mp4`    | **libx264** (H.264) | **aac**        |\n| **`archive`**  | `.mkv`    | **libx265** (H.265/HEVC) | **flac**       |\n| **`gif`**      | `.gif`    | *(palette-based, no standard video codec)* | *(none)*       |\n\n### Details on each profile\n\n1. **`web`** — Targets web-friendly playback. Encodes video with **libx264** into an **MP4** container at 720p (1280×720) with a 2 Mbps target bitrate and **AAC** audio.\n\n2. **`archive`** — Targets high-quality archival. Encodes video with **libx265** (HEVC) into an **MKV** (Matroska) container at the source resolution, CRF 18 (visually near-lossless), with lossless **FLAC** audio.\n\n3. **`gif`** — Produces an animated **GIF** (no separate video/audio codecs; GIF uses its own palette-based encoding internally). It scales to 480px wide and runs at 12 fps. The README notes this is a single-pass palette generation approach with a known quality limitation.\n\nUsers can customize or add more profiles by editing the `profiles.toml` file.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 392, "prompt_tokens": 7872, "total_tokens": 8264, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 14, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 6784, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0008387424, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0004977024, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00034104}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780864146-wyh4fwwO96dWc2AVfFc9", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3c6-5ae5-73b2-8436-86d693f4bd88-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7872, "output_tokens": 392, "total_tokens": 8264, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 6784}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 14}}}}]}}}
